action.description: `init` is triggered every time a slide is loaded. `entity_loaded` is triggered when the editor's main entity is loaded. `sharejs_connected` is triggered when a connection with ShareJS has been established while in case ShareJS is not used for the editor, the more generic `doc_connected` is triggered. `links_rendered` is triggered when all the links (references, media, and rich text embeds / entry hyperlinks) in a slide have been fetched and rendered. `fully_interactive` is trigger when both the links have rendered and the entry has become editable (i.e. ShareJS has connected).

link_count.description: The total number of links (reference links, media field assets, rich text embedded block and inline entries, rich text embedded block assets, and rich text hyperlinked entries) in the entry on initial load

link_field_editor_instance_count.description: The overall number of reference and media field instances in an individual entry (1 locale field = 1 instance)

load_ms.description: Number of milliseconds since the initial load of the entry

rich_text_editor_instance_count.description: The overall number of rich text editor instances in an individual entry (1 locale field editor = 1 instance)

slide_level.description: Level of the entry editor within the slides (zero-indexed, -1 if the slide was closed at the time the event is triggered)

slide_uuid.description: ID uniquely identifying the slide instance - does NOT uniquely identify the entry

slides_controller_uuid.description: ID uniquely identifying the overall session and therefore all slides loaded around the same time within the same browser tab

total_slide_count.description: The total number of slides open when the entry is initially loaded, default = 0 if there are no slides

experiment_id.description: The experiment name the current user is part of

experiment_variation.description: The experiment variation the current user is assigned to

content_type_id.description: Content type ID of the linked entity the action was performed on. `null` in case of an asset.

entity_id.description: ID of the linked entity the action was performed on.

entity_type.description: Type of the linked entity the action was performed on.

event_type.description: The action performed on the linked entity.

parent_entry_id.description: Entry ID of the entry with the field containing the linked entity which the event is about.

parent_field_path.description: `${FIELD_ID}:${LOCALE_CODE}` on the `parent_entry_id` that contains the linked  entity which the event is about. ID/code are public CMA identifiers, not internal CF IDs.
